UID:edJtLrum_KU5pV9LI7-_2
SUMMARY:Slow Flow Community Yoga
DTSTAMP:20260326T160823Z
DTSTART:20260331T233000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, March 31\, 2026\, 4:30 - 5:30pm\n\nJoin us for all-le
	vels slow flow community yoga.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nGreenwood Branch\n\nRo
	om Location: Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not re
	quired.\n\nDetailed Description: Yoga instructors\n\nLucia Hunt\n\nand\n\n
	Emily Dalgo\n\nprovide slow flow yoga classes with trauma-informed cueing 
	to make the classes welcoming\, accessible\, and affirming of all bodies a
	nd identities.\, There will be no expectation of certainyogaexperience to 
	attend classes. Modifications will be offered throughout classes\, encoura
	ging people to listen to what feels good in their body and make adjustment
	s as they need and want to.\n\nEvent Logistics: Yoga mats can be provided 
	at each session.\, Free parking is available in the Greenwood Branch parki
	ng garage and on nearby streets.\, Patrons joining this class will be aske
	d to complete a liability waiver by the instructors.\n\nContact Us: If you
	 have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nA
	DA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilit
	ies at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before
	 the event to request accommodations.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/ev
	ents/#/details/slow-flow-community-yoga/18408085/2026-03-31T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/slow-flow-community-yoga/
	18408085/2026-03-31T00
